						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Hanumān temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 165[9], Naḷa, Phālguṇa, śu. 5.</p>						

						<p>Records the renovation of the temple of Āñjanēya and the Garuḍastambha by Śankaraśeṭṭi, son of Nārayaṇaseṭṭi of Yaliśeṭṭlu-gōtra.</p>						

